Multiple Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers exist for Aircall, allowing AI assistants like Claude, Cursor, and ChatGPT to interact with Aircall's API [1][2][3]. These servers provide tools for managing calls, contacts, teams, and conversation intelligence, such as transcripts and AI summaries [1][4][5].

You can integrate these servers using their respective installation methods, such as adding the server configuration to your MCP settings file [6]. For example, to use the server by themobilefirstco, add this to your configuration [1][6]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "themobilefirstco-aircall-mcp-server": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "themobilefirstco-aircall-mcp-server"]
    }
  }
}
```

Other options include servers hosted by platforms like Pipedream or viaSocket, which provide secure, authenticated endpoints for your AI clients [7][2]. Ensure you have the required API credentials, such as `AIRCALL_API_ID` and `AIRCALL_API_TOKEN`, prepared for your chosen implementation [8][6].
